    <thetext>The Memory View&apos;s &quot;Preferences&quot; action menu item should not hard code the set of preferences. Instead, it should filter preferences for those which apply to the memory view, including the preferences of renderings.

Similarly, the &quot;Table Rendering Preferences&quot; item should be removed from the view&apos;s action menu. 

Today there are three methods of accessing Memory View preferences:
    1) Action Menu -&gt; Preferences
    2) Action Menu -&gt; Table Rendering Preferences
    3) Window -&gt; Preferences -&gt; ... third party rendering pages ...</thetext>
